    "about" => "{"en":"<h2><span style=\"font-family:Jost;\"><strong>Build relationships in maternity care and save lives<\/strong><\/span><\/h2><p><span style=\"font-family:Jost;\">Research unequivocally shows that providing a woman with the same midwife before, during and after birth, results in less preterm birth, fetal death and other complications.<\/span><\/p><p><span style=\"font-family:Jost;\">This course explains why we need relationship-based care in maternity services.     "requirements" => "{"en":"<h2><strong>Who is the course for?<\/strong><\/h2><p>This course is designed for anyone interested in improving maternity care, including midwives, doctors, other health professionals, planners and policy makers, and consumers of maternity care (parents).<\/p>"}"
    "outcomes" => "{"en":"<h2 style=\"text-align:center;\"><strong>What topics will you cover?<\/strong><\/h2><ul><li>The current state of maternity care and its effect on women, babies and families, as well as midwives, other health professionals, and the health service<\/li><li>The case for reform \u2013 why moving to a relationship-based maternity care model significantly improves outcomes across all areas<\/li><li>The evidence behind the efficacy of relationship-based maternity care \u2013 it really does save lives<\/li><li>What relationship-based care involves - the overarching principles and what it means in the context of maternity care<\/li><li>An outline of the relationship framework (organisational model) that best facilitates quality relationship-based care<\/li><li>Demonstrations of relationship-based maternity care in practice<\/li><li>Affecting change from a grassroots level - the power of individuals and groups<\/li><li>How you can help \u2013 practical ways to help make relationship-based care available in your area<\/li><\/ul><h2><strong>Learning on this course<\/strong><\/h2><p>On every step of the course you can meet other learners, share your ideas and join in with active discussions in the comments.<\/p><h2><strong>What will you achieve?<\/strong><\/h2><p>By the end of the course, you\u2018ll be able to...<\/p><ul><li>Summarise the key problems in the current provision of maternity care<\/li><li>Explain what a relationship framework for maternity services is<\/li><li>Justify why a relationship framework for maternity services can produce better outcomes for mother, baby, maternity care providers, and society<\/li><li>Describe the organisational model that can facilitate relationship-based care for maternity services<\/li><li>Develop a plan for action you or your community could implement to begin to affect change in this area<\/li><\/ul><figure class=\"media\"><div data-oembed-url=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=LJrI5xxtqLQ\"><div style=\"position: relative;\"><iframe src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/LJrI5xxtqLQ\" style=\"position: relative; width: 100%; height: 300px; top: 0; left: 0;\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; encrypted-media\" allowfullscreen=\"\"><\/iframe><\/div><\/div><\/figure>"}"
